              </summary>
              <div class="hw-family-body">
                <p>Nonlinear dynamics of the IKI series. Treats keystroke timing as output of a complex adaptive system. Organized into nine theoretical sub-families spanning complexity, structure, causality, and mode decomposition.</p>
